    thinking: "**Verifying Library Dependencies**\n\nI\'ve just finished verifying the server-side libraries! I\'ve created `/src/types.ts`, `/server/db.ts`, `/server/tcxParser.ts`, and `/server.ts`. Everything looks to be in order with the TSX import of ES modules using `.js` relative imports.\n\n\n**Structuring Frontend Components**\n\nI\'m now focused on the frontend structure. I\'ve decided on React with Vite and Tailwind. I\'m building modular subcomponents: `Dashboard`, `Chat`, and `History` with a file uploader, all in the `/src/components` folder, to ensure good modularity and prevent token limit issues. I\'ll make sure each component follows the \"Modularity & Token Limit Management\" guidelines.\n\n\n**Listing Dashboard Icons**\n\nI\'m currently compiling a list of Lucide icons for the dashboard and other components. I\'ve selected icons for Calories (`Flame`), Heart Rate (`Heart`), Running (`Activity`), History (`Calendar`), Distance (`Compass`), Duration (`Clock`), TCX Upload (`UploadCloud`), Chat Send (`Send`), AI Coach (`Sparkles`), Clear chat (`Trash2`), Groq Fast Mode (`Zap`), Premium (`Trophy`), Stats improvement (`TrendingUp`), Model indicators (`Cpu`), Garmin Device (`Smartphone`), Done/Success (`CheckCircle`), and Lap dropdowns (`ChevronDown`, `ChevronUp`). I\'ve verified that all necessary packages are installed, so I can start crafting the animated SVG charts. My next step is to build the `src/components/Dashboard.tsx` component and decide on the statistics and metrics that will be displayed.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create `/src/components/Dashboard.tsx`. This component implements the running statistics dashboard with elegant animated cards (km, hours, pace, HR), custom visual SVG graphs tracking training progression (distance & pace), and a recent activities panel transitioning directly into the full history."
